## 🗃️ Data

The raw data files are **not included** in this repository due to data sharing agreements. Please refer to [`data/README_data.md`](data/README_data.md) for:
- Full variable descriptions and units
- Data sources and access links
- Instructions for replicating the merged dataset

The merged dataset (`Lassa_Final_Merged_Dataset.csv`) is generated automatically by running the pipeline with the two source files.

---

## 📈 Key Findings

- **Soil moisture** and **relative humidity** are the strongest negative predictors of Lassa fever incidence across all six states (Spearman ρ = −0.50 to −0.64)
- A **1–2 week lag** is the optimal forecast window for early warning across all states
- **Taraba** shows the strongest soil moisture signal (ρ = −0.637, p < 10⁻⁴⁷)
- **Random Forest** outperforms the SARIMA climate-naïve baseline in 4 of 6 states, demonstrating the value added by climate predictors
- All Granger causality tests confirm temporal precedence of climate variables over case counts (p < 0.05)

